Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%labels
    Author backup-integrity-setup
    Description "Initial state for the Backup-Integrity exercise"

%post
    set -e

    # Update package index and install required tools
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        openssh-client \
        ca-certificates \
        git \
        locales

    # Install pytest for the evaluation suite
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # Create the dedicated working directory structure
    mkdir -p /home/user/data_backup/2023-11-01

    # Seed files with the exact byte contents required by the tests
    # 1. db.sql  -> 3 bytes "abc"
    printf 'abc' > /home/user/data_backup/2023-11-01/db.sql

    # 2. photos.tar.gz  -> 5 bytes "hello"
    printf 'hello' > /home/user/data_backup/2023-11-01/photos.tar.gz

    # 3. docs.zip -> empty file
    : > /home/user/data_backup/2023-11-01/docs.zip

    # Adjust permissions so the non-root runtime user can read everything
    chmod -R a+rX /home/user

    # We purposely do NOT create:
    #   * /home/user/.ssh
    #   * /home/user/backup_integrity
    # so that the student task starts from a clean state.

    # Clean apt caches to keep the image lean
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Ensure Python and pip are in PATH for all users
    export PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:$PATH

%runscript
    # Default command: open a shell so the automated agent can operate
    exec /bin/bash

%help
    This Apptainer image provides the pristine starting environment for the
    “backup-integrity” exercise. It contains:
      • The seed backup files under /home/user/data_backup/2023-11-01
      • Python 3 and pytest for automated evaluation
      • ssh-keygen (from openssh-client) for key-pair generation

    No SSH keys or integrity-report artefacts exist yet; students are expected
    to create them during the task.